<h2 id="key-features">🔑 Key Features That Actually Matter</h2>

Not every feature in a software platform delivers real value. Some exist purely for marketing checkboxes. Here's what actually moves the needle for serious investors:

<h3>Property Import & Data Population</h3>

DealCheck integrates with major listing platforms including Zillow, Redfin, Realtor.com, and MLS systems. You paste a listing URL, and the platform pulls property details, photos, and estimated values automatically. This alone saves 10-15 minutes per deal analysis. Across 200 analyzed deals per year, that's 50+ hours recovered.

The import isn't perfect—you'll still need to verify numbers and add your own assumptions—but eliminating manual data entry removes both time waste and transcription errors.

<h3>Comprehensive Deal Analysis</h3>

The analysis engine handles metrics that matter: cash-on-cash return, cap rate, gross rent multiplier, debt service coverage ratio, internal rate of return, and net present value. You can model financing scenarios including conventional loans, commercial loans, hard money, seller financing, and cash purchases.

For BRRRR investors, the platform calculates your all-in costs, after-repair value, and refinance scenarios in a single workflow. No more juggling three separate spreadsheets to understand whether a deal actually works.

<h3>Professional Report Generation</h3>

This feature alone justified our switch from custom spreadsheets. DealCheck generates PDF reports that look like they came from a commercial real estate firm. When you're presenting to lenders, partners, or your own investment committee, professional presentation creates confidence.

The reports include property photos, financial projections, sensitivity analysis, and clear assumption documentation. We've had lenders comment positively on report quality—a small thing that smooths the financing process.

<h3>Portfolio Tracking & Performance Monitoring</h3>

Once you close on a property, DealCheck transitions from analysis tool to portfolio tracker. You can monitor actual performance against projections, track equity growth, and maintain a centralized record of all properties.

For operators managing 10+ properties, this eliminates the scattered data problem. No more digging through emails, folders, and spreadsheets to understand your portfolio's current state. Learn more about [consolidating your business data](/guides/business-intelligence-tools-2026) for similar multi-location challenges.

<h3>Rehab Cost Estimator</h3>

The built-in rehab estimator helps standardize renovation budgeting. You can create custom cost templates based on your market and preferred contractors, then apply them consistently across deal analyses. This prevents the optimism bias that kills flip profits—underestimating rehab costs by 20% turns a profitable flip into a breakeven nightmare.

